esqlQuery.esql:
// Alert when Kubernetes nodes report disk pressure.
//
// What triggers this alert:
// Node running out of disk space — may evict pods or become unschedulable.
//
// Common causes:
// Log accumulation, image buildup, large temporary files, insufficient disk capacity.
//
// Action needed:
// Clean up disk space, remove unused images, increase volume size, check pod logs.
//
// To scope to a cluster, add: AND `orchestrator.cluster.name` == "YOUR_CLUSTER"
TS metrics-kubernetes.node-*
| WHERE `kubernetes.node.status.disk_pressure` == "true"
| STATS doc_count = COUNT(*)
  BY `orchestrator.cluster.name`, `kubernetes.node.name`
| WHERE doc_count > 0
